{
  "texts": [
    "LimitationsSome of the limitations and challenges associated with the application of Shapley value in ML include: 1.",
    "Computational Complexity: Although efforts have been made to develop fast approximation methods to alleviate the computational costs of computing Shapley values, it remains a computationally expensive task, especially when dealing with large-scale models and datasets. 2.",
    "Ambiguity in Feature Interactions: Shapley value assumes that contributions of individual features are independent of their interactions with other features.",
    "However, in reality, features may interact with each other in complex ways, leading to challenges in accurately attributing contributions. 3.",
    "Model Sensitivity: Shapley value can be sensitive to changes in the model or training data."
  ]
}